
[1]integument

   INTEG'UMENT, n. [L. integumentum, intego, to cover; in and tego. See
   Deck.] That which naturally invests or covers another thing; but
   appropriately and chiefly, in anatomy, a covering which invests the
   body, as the skin, or a membrane that invests a particular part. The
   skin of seeds and the shells of crustaceous animals are denominated
   integuments.
